User API endpoint: https://api.example.com/users

- Endpoint: GET (list users). Returns the list of users fetched from the server.
- Authorization: requires the authorization token. Should be sent in a request header for every request except `POST /login` and `POST /signup`.
- Parameters: limit
- Sample request - https://api.example.com/users?limit=10 (list 10 users, default to 25)
- Response code is 2xx - success
    - body: { "id": String, “username” : String, ... }
- Sample response - 200, {“id”: ”548d7793-c0ae-408b-a8bf-36f909031c2e”, “username” : “John Doe”}

- Endpoint: POST (sign up). Takes user data as JSON in the body and returns the authentication token if successful. If the request is invalid, it should return 4xx error code
    - body: { "name": String } // mandatory field. must be unique across all users.
    - body: { "email": String } // email address of the user
    - body: { "password": String } // user’s password
- Sample response - If successful, returns 200, {"token":"..."} in JSON format
    - Sample request - https://api.example.com/login (returns a session token)
        - request header should have a token as  “sessionToken”
        - If session expired or invalid error code returned, this endpoint should return a new one
- Response codes: 
    - 409 – The user data is already used in the database
    - 2xx success

